def: Not apposite; not fit or suitable; not pertinent.-- In*ap"po*site*ly, adv.
Doubly ternate, as when a petiole has three ternate leaflets.-- Bi*ter"nate*ly, adv. Gray.
An insect of the family Coccid√¶, which infests the bark oftrees and vines.
Fit for market; such as is usually sold in market, or such aswill bring the ordinary price; as, merchantable wheat; sometimes, atechnical designation for a particular kind or class.
To recognize or judge in advance; to forebode. [Obs.] Udall.Laugh at your misery, as foredeeming you An idle meteor. J. Webster.
Saturnian; -- applied to the North Polar Sea. [R.] Milton.
To feel or express undue care and anxiety; to manifestdisquietude or pain; to be fretful; to chafe; as, the child worries;the horse worries.
